This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The summary below covers the earlier portion of the conversation.

Summary:
1. Primary Request and Intent:
   - **Request 1**: Create a complete markdown editor with live preview, consisting of 4 files in `/Users/yimtaejong/omc-verification/disable-omc/run3/`:
     - `index.html`: Split-pane layout with toolbar (Bold, Italic, Bold+Italic, H1-H3, Link, Image, Code, Code Block, UL, OL, Blockquote, HR) and Export HTML button
     - `style.css`: Professional dark theme, responsive split panes, draggable resizer, GitHub markdown style
     - `markdown-parser.js`: Complete markdown parser (no external libraries) supporting all standard elements
     - `editor.js`: Real-time preview, toolbar actions with cursor positioning, drag-to-resize, keyboard shortcuts (Ctrl+B/I/K), localStorage auto-save, Export HTML
   - **Request 2**: Create `editor.test.js` with comprehensive tests using plain assertions (no framework), covering: parser elements, edge cases, toolbar actions, localStorage, Export HTML. Run with `node editor.test.js`
   - **Request 3**: Review all created files for parser correctness, XSS prevention, toolbar cursor position handling, resize drag edge cases, memory leaks, accessibility. Fix any bugs found. Run tests again and report results.

2. Key Technical Concepts:
   - Pure JavaScript markdown parser (no external libs) using regex-based tokenization
   - IIFE (Immediately Invoked Function Expression) module pattern for encapsulation
   - XSS prevention: `escapeHtml()` applied upfront in `parseInline()` before all regex transforms
   - URL safety: `isSafeUrl()` blocks `javascript:`, `vbscript:`, `data:` URI schemes with entity decoding
   - `rel="noopener noreferrer"` on generated links to prevent tabnapping
   - DOM mocking in Node.js for browser-based editor testing (no JSDOM)
   - `eval()` + `global.xxx = yyy` pattern to load browser scripts in Node.js test environment
   - `Object.defineProperty` to override read-only `navigator` global in Node.js v23
   - `vm.runInThisContext` alternative considered but `eval` + global assignment used
   - localStorage mock with plain object store
   - Content Security Policy (CSP) meta tag for defense in depth
   - ARIA accessibility: `aria-label`, `aria-hidden="true"` on decorative SVGs
   - Cursor position management after toolbar actions (`setSelectionRange`)
   - Debounced auto-save with `setTimeout`/`clearTimeout`
   - Split-pane drag resizer with mouse/touch events, 20%–80% clamping

3. Files and Code Sections:
   - **`/Users/yimtaejong/omc-verification/disable-omc/run3/markdown-parser.js`**
     - Core markdown parser, fully rewritten to fix critical XSS bugs
     - Added `isSafeUrl()` function after `escapeHtml()`:
       ```javascript
       function isSafeUrl(url) {
         const decoded = url
           .replace(/&amp;/g, '&').replace(/&lt;/g, '<').replace(/&gt;/g, '>')
           .replace(/&quot;/g, '"').replace(/&#39;/g, "'")
           .replace(/&#(\d+);/g, (_, c) => String.fromCharCode(Number(c)))
           .replace(/&#x([\da-f]+);/gi, (_, c) => String.fromCharCode(parseInt(c, 16)));
         const trimmed = decoded.trim().toLowerCase();
         return !/^(javascript|vbscript|data):/i.test(trimmed);
       }
       ```
     - Modified `parseInline()` — `escapeHtml()` now called upfront BEFORE all regex transforms:
       ```javascript
       function parseInline(text) {
         text = protectEscapes(text);
         // SECURITY: escape all raw HTML first
         text = escapeHtml(text);
         // Inline code — content already escaped
         text = text.replace(/`([^`\n]+?)`/g, '<code>$1</code>');
         // Images — add isSafeUrl check
         text = text.replace(/!\[([^\]]*)\]\(([^)]+?)(?:\s+"([^"]*)")?\)/g, (match, alt, src, title) => {
           if (!isSafeUrl(src)) return match;
           const titleAttr = title ? ` title="${title}"` : '';
           return `<img src="${src}" alt="${alt}"${titleAttr}>`;
         });
         // Links — add isSafeUrl check + rel="noopener noreferrer"
         text = text.replace(/\[([^\]]+)\]\(([^)]+?)(?:\s+"([^"]*)")?\)/g, (match, linkText, href, title) => {
           if (!isSafeUrl(href)) return match;
           const titleAttr = title ? ` title="${title}"` : '';
           return `<a href="${href}" rel="noopener noreferrer"${titleAttr}>${linkText}</a>`;
         });
         // bold/italic/strikethrough regexes unchanged — $1 already escaped
         ...
       }
       ```
     - Fixed `parseCodeBlock()` to accept `fenceChar` parameter, use correct closing fence, and handle unclosed fences:
       ```javascript
       function parseCodeBlock(lines, startIndex, lang, fenceChar) {
         const fencePrefix = fenceChar === '~' ? '~~~' : '```';
         let codeLines = [];
         let i = startIndex + 1;
         while (i < lines.length && !lines[i].startsWith(fencePrefix)) {
           codeLines.push(lines[i]);
           i++;
         }
         // Unclosed fence: treat opening line as plain text
         if (i >= lines.length) {
           return { html: `<p>${escapeHtml(lines[startIndex])}</p>\n`, nextIndex: startIndex + 1 };
         }
         ...
       }
       ```
     - Updated `parse()` to pass `fenceChar` to `parseCodeBlock`:
